26/01/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Miroslav Lajcak, newly appointed by the EU to mediate the political crisis in Albania, kicked off his visit by meeting with President Bamir Topi on Wednesday (January 26th).
They discussed the situation in the country in the aftermath of Friday's deadly violence and steps that can be taken to resolve the crisis.
Lajcak is also due to meet with Prime Minister Sali Berisha and opposition leader Edi Rama.
(Top Channel, Top News, News 24 - 26/01/11)
